title: Wider CityLink and Tullamarine Freeway will pump tens of thousands more cars into suburbs
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Wider CityLink and Tullamarine Freewa... Wider CityLink and Tullamarine Freeway will pump tens of thousands more cars into suburbs 14 min ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Widening CityLink and the Tullamarine Freeway will trigger huge increases in traffic across Melbourne's north-west and the inner city, with the number of trips on some main roads in the suburbs set to soar more than 200 per cent. The Andrews government's traffic modelling for the $1.3 billion project , seen by The Age , forecasts that traffic will become much heavier on virtually all roads that connect with the freeway.
